<TITLE> SC: No bail for Mamun </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com)  A five member bench of the Supreme Court on Monday ordered that controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun should not be granted bail in relation to a money laundering case. In doing so, it upheld a decision originally given on Jan 31 by an appellate division judge, sitting alone in his chambers, that had temporarily stayed a bail order granted three days earlier by the High Court on Jan 28. The five-member Appellate Division headed by chief justice Md Fazlul Karim gave its order on Monday following a full hearing of the government appeal against the bail order granted by the High Court. Barrister Rafique-ul-Huq represented Mamun in the hearing. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case against Mamun on Oct 26 last year on charges of laundering Tk 20 crore. Mamun, who faces a further 20 cases, is known as a close associate of Tarique Rahman, elder son of opposition leader Khaleda Zia. b
